==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zincography
<hw>Zin*cog"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Zinco-</ets> + <ets>-graphy</ets>.]</ety> <def>The art or
process of engraving or etching on zinc, in which the design is left in
relief in the style of a wood cut, the rest of the ground being eaten
away by acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zincoid</ent>⟦br⟧
